{"word":"ἀναίσθητος","slug":"ἀναίσθητος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀναίσθητος</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>insensate, unfeeling</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:— <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>ἀναισθήτως ἔχειν</el> <i>to be indifferent</i>, <b><a href='S:Isocrates'>Isocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>senseless, wanting tact, stupid</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>: —<el>τὸ ἀναίσθητον</el> <i>insensibility</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>unfelt</i>, <el>θάνατος</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}